@niclash That's good news and bad news. 

The good part: anything that makes a broken DB work again is worth looking into.

The bad part: I'm super unsure about `DropTableOnRebuildError`. This feature was added in the https://github.com/rchunping/goleveldb fork of goleveldb and it seems to just drop data. There are no guarantees if you do that. You might as well drop the whole DB.
